14/05/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer described Bulgaria and Romania as serious and reliable allies, as he launched his tour of the new NATO member countries with visits to Bucharest and Sofia on Thursday (13 May).
In both capitals, de Hoop Scheffer stressed that reforms in the respective defence sectors should continue and that the two states are expected to play important roles in transforming the Alliance.
In other news, the Bulgarian government approved and forwarded to parliament an agreement to donate weapons, munitions and equipment worth 8m euros to Afghanistan.
The donation, made at the request of the UN, would support the newly established Afghan security forces.
(Rompres, Dnevnik, 24 Chasa - 14/05/04;
Mediafax, BNT - 13/05/04)
